'''Kashima Shrine''' ('''Kashima Shrine''', かしまじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945}} in Shimoda-nishi, {{ill|lt=Kashiba|Q696643|WD=Q696643}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|WD=Q131287}}.

It is the shrine from which the name of Kashiba City is said to derive<ref name="city-name">[https://www.city.kashiba.lg.jp/soshiki/5/3826.html 香芝市の沿革] - Kashiba City</ref>.

=== Overview ===
It is enshrined near west of JR {{ill|lt=Kashiba Station|Q3655907|WD=Q3655907}}, and near north of {{ill|lt=Kintetsu Shimoda Station|Q6414373|WD=Q6414373}} on the {{ill|lt=Kintetsu Osaka Line|Q1052545|WD=Q1052545}}.

Its founding is said to begin in March {{ill|lt=1172|Q19687|WD=Q19687}} ({{ill|lt=Shōan (Japan)|Q1194188|WD=Q1194188|lt=Shōan}} 2), when {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Kamada Masamitsu|1=UNKNOWN}}, son of {{ill|lt=Kamada Masakiyo|Q11651065|WD=Q11651065}} (a retainer of {{ill|lt=Minamoto no Yoshitomo|Q532301|WD=Q532301}}), invited the deity from {{ill|lt=Kashima Jingū|Q706499|WD=Q706499}} in {{ill|lt=Hitachi Province|Q1055353|WD=Q1055353}} (present-day {{ill|lt=Ibaraki Prefecture|Q83273|WD=Q83273}})<ref name="yuisho">[https://kashiba-no-kashima.org/top-page/history/ 由緒] - Kashima Shrine</ref><ref name="city-muse">[https://www.city.kashiba.lg.jp/uploaded/attachment/1653.pdf 鹿島神社] - Kashiba Nijō-san Museum</ref>.

There is also a theory that before the founding of this Kashima Shrine, an older local shrine existed here, namely '''Fukamizo Shrine''', one of the {{ill|lt=Shikinaisha in Yamato Province|Q11433427|WD=Q11433427|lt=Shikinaisha of Yamato Province}}<ref name="yuisho"/><ref name="city-muse"/>.

=== Enshrined deity ===
