'''Kashima Shrine''' ('''Kashima Shrine''', かしまじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} in Shimoda-nishi, {{ill|lt=Kashiba|Q696643|qid=Q696643|1=Kashiba, Nara}}, {{ill|lt=Nara Prefecture|Q131287|qid=Q131287|1=Nara Prefecture}}.

It is the shrine from which the name of Kashiba City is said to derive<ref name="city-name">[https://www.city.kashiba.lg.jp/soshiki/5/3826.html 香芝市の沿革] - Kashiba City</ref>.

=== Overview ===
It is enshrined near west of JR {{ill|lt=Kashiba Station|Q3655907|qid=Q3655907|1=Kashiba Station}}, and near north of {{ill|lt=Kintetsu Shimoda Station|Q6414373|qid=Q6414373|1=Kintetsu Shimoda Station}} on the {{ill|lt=Kintetsu Osaka Line|Q1052545|qid=Q1052545|1=Osaka Line}}.

Its founding is said to begin in March {{ill|lt=1172|Q19687|qid=Q19687|1=1172}} ({{ill|lt=Shōan (Japan)|Q1194188|qid=Q1194188|lt=Shōan|1=Jōan (era)}} 2), when {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Kamada Masamitsu|1=UNKNOWN}}, son of {{ill|lt=Kamada Masakiyo|Q11651065|qid=Q11651065|1=Kamata Masakiyo}} (a retainer of {{ill|lt=Minamoto no Yoshitomo|Q532301|qid=Q532301|1=Minamoto no Yoshitomo}}), invited the deity from {{ill|lt=Kashima Jingū|Q706499|qid=Q706499|1=Kashima Jingū}} in {{ill|lt=Hitachi Province|Q1055353|qid=Q1055353|1=Hitachi Province}} (present-day {{ill|lt=Ibaraki Prefecture|Q83273|qid=Q83273|1=Ibaraki Prefecture}})<ref name="yuisho">[https://kashiba-no-kashima.org/top-page/history/ 由緒] - Kashima Shrine</ref><ref name="city-muse">[https://www.city.kashiba.lg.jp/uploaded/attachment/1653.pdf 鹿島神社] - Kashiba Nijō-san Museum</ref>.

There is also a theory that before the founding of this Kashima Shrine, an older local shrine existed here, namely '''Fukamizo Shrine''', one of the {{ill|lt=Shikinaisha in Yamato Province|Q11433427|qid=Q11433427|lt=Shikinaisha of Yamato Province|1=List of Shikinaisha in Yamato Province}}<ref name="yuisho"/><ref name="city-muse"/>.

